==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[fabuleux]]'' or Latin ''[[fabulosus]]'' 'celebrated in [[fable]]'.

===Adjective===
'''fabulous'''
#[[Extraordinary]], especially in being very large.
#Very good; [[wonderful]].
#''(chiefly obsolete)'' [[Mythical]] or [[legendary]]; [[incredible]].
#Of the nature of a [[fable]]; [[unhistorical]].

====Related terms====
*[[fable]] (noun)

====Derived terms====
*[[fabulously]] (adverb)
*[[fabulousness]] (noun)

